âš ï¸ Save your EC2 Public IP

## ğŸ’» 2. Connect EC2 Using WSL (Windows)

Copy .pem file into WSL:

cp /mnt/c/Program\ Files/WSL/pemfile .

Connect to EC2 via SSH:

sudo ssh -i pemfile machine@<ec2-instance-ip>

Update your system:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

## ğŸŒ 3. Enable HTTP Access (Port 80)

Go to Security Groups

Edit Inbound Rules

Add rule:

Type: HTTP  
Port: 80  
Source: 0.0.0.0/0 (Anywhere IPv4)

## âš™ï¸ 4. Install Nginx on EC2
sudo apt install nginx -y
sudo systemctl start nginx

## ğŸŒ 5. Access Your Server

Open your browser and go to:

http://<your-ec2-ip>/

